Good Afternoon Pacheco Union District Families,

This message is to inform you that the Pacheco Union School District will be suspending face to face instruction starting tomorrow, Tuesday, 3/17/20-Tuesday, 4/14/20. Please stay tuned for more information regarding instruction opportunities as well as food services during this temporary suspension of face to face instruction. We appreciate your patience as we work through all of the details. Please continue to check our district website and app for new information.

shared_text:
Judy Flores is with Caryn Emerson and 3 others.
February 3 at 11:29 PM ·

Today, the Shasta County Office of Education hosted an event honoring students who are succeeding in spite of the odds. The event recognized 15 students, as young as third grade up through seniors in high school. Each of these students has overcome significant challenges and is thriving in school and with their peers. It was great to hear each story and celebrate the growth achieved by each one.

A summary of each student's story is included with their individual photo.

Special thanks to each one who nominated a student for this award!

Welcome to the 2015-16 school year,
School starts on Tuesday, August 18, at 8:25 AM.
Class rosters will be posted Thursday, August 13th at 1:00 PM.
A meet and greet will take place Monday, August 17, from 2:30-3:30 PM.
The entire Pacheco School staff are very excited to see your smiling faces. It is going to be a great year!
See you soon,
Mr. Provence

No Minimum Day Monday, 6/1/15
This is reminder that Monday, June 1, is NOT a minimum day.

Double Minimum Day Thursday, 6/4/15
Thursday, June 4, is the last day of school and it will be a DOUBLE minimum day. Your student will be released 2 hours earlier than the regular dismissal time. If you have any questions, please contact the school office. Thank you and have a wonderful evening!

post_text: The Governing Board of the Pacheco Union School District has four vacancies on the Citizens Bond Oversight Committee. Therefore, the Governing Board is seeking qualified, interested individuals to serve on a committee of community leaders which will serve as the independent Citizens Bond Oversight Committee for the implementation of Measure B School Facilities Bond program. Each appointment is for two years. If you are interested, more information can be found on the District's website.
